<span id="freeTextContainer14534330655045511980">I am very cross. This is yet another book that I rated and reviewed and has disappeared from my shelves. I wonder if it happened when some librarian decided to add series information to it and thereby change the title? If it is no. 1 in a series there has to be a no. 2. There isn&apos;t. It isn&apos;t a series. According to Wikipedia,<br/><br/>&quot;A Canticle for Leibowitz is based on three short stories Miller contributed to The Magazine of Fantasy &amp; Science Fiction.[1][2] It is the only novel published by the author </span>
  <span id="freeText14534330655045511980" style="display:none">I am very cross. This is yet another book that I rated and reviewed and has disappeared from my shelves. I wonder if it happened when some librarian decided to add series information to it and thereby change the title? If it is no. 1 in a series there has to be a no. 2. There isn't. It isn't a series. According to Wikipedia,<br /><br />"A Canticle for Leibowitz is based on three short stories Miller contributed to The Magazine of Fantasy &amp; Science Fiction.[1][2] It is the only novel published by the author during his lifetime.."<br /><br />That's pretty conclusive isn't it? <br /><br />Maybe it wasn't that, maybe it is the GR monster that GR are content to let feed on our shelves. <br /><br /></span>
